Albion Online is a sandbox MMORPG that offers a truly cross-platform experience. Here, you can do anything. After choosing a character and completing the tutorial, you’ll emerge into the world of Albion, full of dangers and riches. And the scariest thing in it is not monsters, but other players like you. Imagine: you decided to farm solo dungeons, made it to the cave, went in, started cleaning, then suddenly somebody killed you from the back, and here you are, standing in the middle of the city without your equipment or loot. That’s right — if another player kills you in Red or Black zones, your gear, weapons, and other items from the inventory are gone. Sure, you can level up, collect resources, complete instanced dungeons, and even skip corrupted ones in Yellow zones, but this is completely unprofitable. For example, you get a +100% loot bonus for mobs in Black zones in comparison with similar mobs in Yellow or safe zones. Almost any activity, from fishing to farming, will bring more profit if you do it in zones where you can be killed. Of course, there is content for PvE players too: in Albion Online, you can buy an island, make your own “Farm Frenzy”, breed animals, and plant carrots. But it’s only available with a premium account, so we suggest you buy Albion Online Top Up and unlock all the possibilities for a comfortable gaming experience. You’ll receive books that will help you quickly upgrade your skills, 50% reduced Market tax, 50% Silver and loot from mobs, and up to 100% resource-gathering bonuses. To ensure that death doesn’t interrupt your adventures, you can buy gold and trade it for silver via the in-game Gold Exchange. Silver will give you access to any item on the auction. And don’t forget about character customization options and mount skins, which won’t be lost even if you get killed and will always please the eye.
